## OWASP Top 10 — Quick Reference

| # | Risk | Primary Mitigation |
|---|------|--------------------|
| A01 | Broken Access Control | Enforce authz at service layer; deny by default |
| A02 | Cryptographic Failures | TLS everywhere; strong hashing; encrypt PII |
| A03 | Injection | Parameterised queries; input validation; escape output |
| A04 | Insecure Design | Threat model early; defence in depth |
| A05 | Security Misconfiguration | Hardened defaults; remove unused features; scan configs |
| A06 | Vulnerable Components | Audit dependencies; keep updated |
| A07 | Auth Failures | Strong passwords; MFA; rate limiting; secure sessions |
| A08 | Integrity Failures | Verify signatures; use lockfiles; review CI pipeline |
| A09 | Logging Failures | Log security events; protect logs; set up alerts |
| A10 | SSRF | Allowlist outbound URLs; block internal IP ranges |
